y^2+2xyz=1
x
x
y^2
y^2 + 2xyz = 1 \implies y^2 - y^2 + 2xyz = 1 - y^2 \implies 2xyz = 1 - y^2
2yz
x = \frac{2xyz}{2yz} = \frac{1 - y^2}{2yz}
\begin{align} \qquad\qquad\qquad\qquad y^2+2xyz&=1\\\\ 2xyz&=1-y^2\\\\ x\cdot(2yz)&=1-y^2\\\\ x&=\frac{1-y^2}{2yz} &\small(\text{assuming }y,z\neq 0) \end{align}
